✨Changing to a NEW ball of yarn - Crochet ✨

Tutorial video showing you what to do when it’s time to switch yarn. Have you reached the end of the ball you’re working with?? Or maybe it’s time to change colors? This video will show you how to get it done! 

Both the Double Crochet scarf project and Single Crochet scarf project are shown in this video (in that order ☺️)!
@emmerylan @lionbrandyarn #kickingitwithemmeandkirsten #crochetersofinstagram

Here is our VERY BEGINNER SINGLE CROCHET SCARF TUTORIAL!!
⠀
You will need 2 balls of @lionbrandyarn Wool-ease Thick & Quick and a 16mm crochet hook! ⠀
⠀
💕Post pics and make sure to use our hashtag #kickingitwithemmeandkirsten so we can see your progress! 

@emmerylan and I like to make our Knit/Crochet Along posts identical so you get the same information across the board, but I am breaking from that and running free 🙆🏼‍♀️ for just a moment...

Can we please give Emme a 🙌🏼 in the comment section for what a FANTASTIC job she does on the tutorial videos?? A lot of work goes into getting these Craft Alongs going. First thing we had to do before we could post anything for this one was to test out the patterns with the yarn substitutions we were going to recommend. 😬🤦🏼‍♀️😳 I think we’ve crocheted the Sundance Crossbody enough times to solidify the pattern’s existence in our brains. 😆 We-love-every-minute of the planning and work. ♥️ When we first started doing Knit Alongs last year, Emme and I quickly realized where our strengths are. I do the graphics and all of the text you guys read - Emme puts her brilliant teaching skills to work for these tutorial videos - then together we do Instagram Stories and Live chats. 🥰 For those of you who also have children, you know how difficult it can be to find a moment to yourself during the day, let alone 30 minutes to record a video for Instagram...after you’ve made sure your hands don’t look like 💩 and then set up your work station. So props to my bestie for another great tutorial. I don’t know how you find the time, but I’m so happy you do because my tutorial videos would suck. Btw, my favorite moment from this video is when Emme says “We took a moment, we’re super proud of ourselves, and we move on.” #crochetersofinstagram #singlecrochetstitch💕 @emmerylan

node.text: Thought I’d show you guys how I keep my current projects handy and ready to go (these days I’m just going between my living room and bedroom, but at least my yarn and supplies are packed up nicely and organized!) Currently using those needles on both of the Top Gun Bombers that I’m making (that pattern is by @knitatude - check her patterns out. She’s a genius and her instructions are extremely easy to understand.) I hope everyone is staying safe at home! If you’re interested in learning how to knit check out the link in my bio for a “very beginner” pattern and supply list from myself and @emmerylan!! Never a better time to learn something new than while we’re all stuck at home. xoxo 😘

node.text:
First, thank you for all of the well wishes I’ve received over the last few days. 🥰

Little bit of info for those who are wondering...
 I spent the last few years having random health issues that I disregarded as side affects to my medications or just something I was experiencing due to age. When I went to get an MRI for some severe neck pain I have been experiencing for the last few months (I assumed this neck pain was also causing my frequent “migraines”) my amazingly thorough orthopedist ordered an MRI of my head just to be on the “safe side” - even though that isn’t his area of expertise. 
Truly a great doctor. 
That’s when we stumbled upon a rather large, very full of fluid, cyst that was attached to the lower portion of brain. I feel very fortunate that my situation wasn’t more serious and that I had a wonderful neurosurgeon who immediately knew how to fix it. I’m not gonna lie, brain surgery had me nervous, but I’m immensely thankful to my family, friends, and incredible “work family” who have been supportive, kind and loving during a time when I’ve been feeling a lot of emotions. Work is a great place to be everyday and for the 2 months leading up to my surgery I found a lot of comfort being around the people I’ve worked beside for so many years. I’m excited to get back to it after my recovery. (Yes, they shaved a portion of my head, so please no comments if you don’t like my hair. It’s temporary.)
Again, thank you to everyone for sending positive vibes my way. It’s not gone unnoticed. ♥️ 

Fun fact: I now firmly believe the new plates in my brain will give me some sort of special ability. Fingers crossed I can suddenly knit a sweater in 1 day. Ooo maybe 1 hour. 😮

As for this picture (trust, you don’t want to see a pic of me at the moment), these are 2 projects I started a few weeks ago and I’m looking forward to finishing them before I return to work. Both are made with @lionbrandyarn (the one on the left is “Hue + Me” and the one on the right is “Heartland”) - it’s obvious I have a specific color palette happening right now. 🤷🏼‍♀️ 

Sending love to all of you guys! ♥️
